## Formatting Rules

- Always begin with the application-grounded success criterion.
- One dimension at a time. Never batch.
- Cite source per treatment (Doshi-Velez, Miller, Lipton, Wachter, Bansal).
- Tradeoff named explicitly per dimension.
- Component scaffolds are concrete, not abstract.
- Anti-pattern check is mandatory before output.
